Description: Limestone stela dated to year 7 of Sheshonq V, recording donation of ten arouras of land of great chief of Libu Tjerpet (?) to Sekhmet, with four and a half incised lines of hieratic below scene of Tjerpet (?) offering to Sekhmet and Heka.
Curator's comments: See Moje, Journal of Egyptian History 4 (2011) 81–98 Spencer, Kom Firin I, pl.89
Bibliographic references: Shaw & Nicholson 1995 / British Museum Dictionary of Ancient Egypt (p162)
Condition: fair - surface scratched, weathered along left part of front
